# Build Stage
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-21-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /build

# Cache dependencies
COPY pom.xml .
RUN mvn dependency:go-offline -B || true

# Copy source and build the application
COPY src ./src
RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests && \
    find target -maxdepth 1 -name "*.jar" ! -name "original-*.jar" -exec cp {} /build/app.jar \;

# Runtime Stage
FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jre-alpine

# Expose required port
EXPOSE 3000

# Install international font packages (for PDF/CJK), curl (for healthcheck), and certificate tools
RUN apk add --no-cache fontconfig ttf-dejavu curl wget ca-certificates

# Import AWS RDS and Azure DigiCert certificates into the Java truststore
RUN wget -qO /tmp/rds-bundle.pem https://truststore.pki.rds.amazonaws.com/global/global-bundle.pem && \
    wget -qO /tmp/azure-digicert.pem https://cacerts.digicert.com/DigiCertGlobalRootG2.crt.pem && \
    # Import Azure DigiCert Global Root G2
    keytool -importcert -trustcacerts -file /tmp/azure-digicert.pem -alias azure-digicert -keystore $JAVA_HOME/lib/security/cacerts -storepass changeit -noprompt && \
    # Split AWS RDS global bundle into individual certificates and import them
    awk 'BEGIN {c=0;} /BEGIN CERTIFICATE/{c++} { print > "/tmp/rds-" c ".pem"}' < /tmp/rds-bundle.pem && \
    for f in /tmp/rds-*.pem; do \
        if grep -q "BEGIN CERTIFICATE" "$f"; then \
            keytool -importcert -trustcacerts -file "$f" -alias "aws-rds-$(basename "$f")" -keystore $JAVA_HOME/lib/security/cacerts -storepass changeit -noprompt; \
        fi; \
    done && \
    # Cleanup temporary certificate files
    rm -rf /tmp/*.pem

# Create non-root user 'app' with UID 1001
RUN addgroup -S -g 1001 appgroup && \
    adduser -S -u 1001 -G appgroup app

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the built JAR file from the builder stage
COPY --from=builder --chown=app:appgroup /build/app.jar /app/app.jar

# Switch to the non-root user
USER app

# Define application healthcheck
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s --start-period=30s --retries=3 \
  CMD curl -fs http://localhost:3000/api/health || exit 1

# Start the application
CMD ["java", "-jar", "/app/app.jar"]
